DUBAI: Saudi fashion house Leem announced on Wednesday the launch of its first spring 2022 capsule collection. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle The new designs will be available in stores throughout the Kingdom, the UAE, and Bahrain, as well as on the Leem app, available in Saudi Arabia. The capsule collection features airy knits – wardrobe staples for the transitional season – that are light and loose in fit.  A post shared by Leem (@leem_global) The designs are also characterized by their metal detailing, such as chain accents and studding found on shoulders and necklines. The trend-led pieces include tassel embroidery, balloon sleeves, and mesh detailing. Mermaid-shaped skirts, crossed with geometric shapes and pleated trims, and floor-skimming maxi dresses, also take center stage. Leem, launched in the Kingdom in 2018, offers modern yet conservative designs that include wide-leg trousers, large sweaters, elegant dresses, and oversized tops. Specializing in unique fabrics and various shapes, its collections are made with the modern woman in mind. 